text: I have the privilege to lead a group of
engineers 25 engineers who are in charge
of doing all the installation planning
for the interiors of the 737 I've been
on a consistent journey of just paving
the way not only for myself but others
that are in the tech industry I was the
first founder of the Nesby chapter on my
campus there were about 10 engineering
students of minority background at the
time there were many challenges getting
to where I am today it started with my
immigration here to the US and since
then it's been an important role for me
and my family to make sure that I serve
as a role model
curiosity is what's going to drive you
forward consistently so be curious be
curious about the space about the
narratives that you hear and also about
the people around you because the the
conversation needs to be where that
diverse dialogue is what's changing the
world and not a limited dialogue of just
the same people always in the
conversation whether it be taken apart
hardware or whether it be getting down
and dirty with my team I would say my
tech superpower is being able to team
and also being able to do or apply my
skills to whatever I'm doing
